{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775886194344,"sessionID":"ses_284f172dcffeXzZ2f78vIZDeZ4","part":{"id":"prt_d7b0e9539001K4BLGMeQhep6vK","messageID":"msg_d7b0e8e21001x53cOspt6CruAB","sessionID":"ses_284f172dcffeXzZ2f78vIZDeZ4","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_159959dc301c49df9e0dfbf2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore AR-037 PCAP analyzer","prompt":"Search the codebase thoroughly for anything related to \"AR-037\", \"PCAP\", \"pcap analyzer\", \"pcap分析器\" in the agentcube project. Look for:\n\n1. Any feature docs, spec files, or planning documents mentioning AR-037\n2. Any PCAP-related source code files\n3. Any example applications related to PCAP analysis\n4. Any TODO files, changelogs, or archive files mentioning this work\n5. Check directories like: docs/, examples/, src/, features/, archives/, changelogs/, etc.\n\nSearch broadly across the entire workspace root at /home/dsj/benchmark and also check the current working directory.\n\nReturn a comprehensive summary of:\n- What files exist related to AR-037 / PCAP analyzer\n- What features were implemented (based on code and docs)\n- What was deferred or left incomplete (based on TODOs, comments, or docs)\n- The overall state of this work","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_284f1558affeWjyQABi7XgNSyq (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nHere is the comprehensive summary of all findings related to **AR-037 / PCAP Analyzer** in the agentcube project:\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Summary: AR-037 -- PCAP Analyzer Example Application\n\n### 1. What Files Exist Related to AR-037 / PCAP Analyzer\n\n#### A. AR-037 Change Request Documents (Primary Workspace)\nLocated at `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-037/`:\n\n| File | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `proposal.md` | AR-037 proposal -- \"PCAP 分析器示例应用\", Module: example, Language: Python, Size: M |\n| `design.md` | Design document (was written during ST-3 stage) |\n| `delta-spec.md` | Delta spec with GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios |\n| `tasks.md` | 13 atomic tasks (T-1 through T-13) with dependency graph |\n\n#### B. Example Application Source Code\nLocated at `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/example/pcap_analyzer/` (underscore variant):\n\n| File | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `pcap_analyzer.py` | Main application -- 565 lines. Contains BOTH a FastAPI web service (with LangChain/LangGraph agents) AND a CLI script (with argparse, scapy-based analysis) |\n| `__init__.py` | Package marker |\n| `requirements.txt` | 15 dependencies (FastAPI, LangChain, LangGraph, paramiko, etc.) |\n| `Dockerfile` | uv-based container image |\n| `deployment.yaml` | Kubernetes Deployment manifest |\n| `README.md` | Usage documentation |\n| `tests/` | Test directory with 3 test files |\n\n#### C. Test Files\nLocated at `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/example/pcap_analyzer/tests/`:\n\n| File | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `test_pcap_analyzer.py` | Tests for configuration, FastAPI app, analyze endpoint |\n| `test_agents.py` | Tests for ReAct agent, planner agent, reporter agent |\n| `test_sandbox_runner.py` | Tests for SandboxRunner class |\n| `__init__.py` | Package marker |\n\n#### D. Integrations Module (References PCAP Analyzer)\nLocated at `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/integrations/`:\n\n| File | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `spec.md` | Integrations spec -- covers BOTH Dify plugin AND PCAP analyzer FastAPI service requirements |\n| `design.md` | Integrations design -- architecture overview for Dify plugin + PCAP analyzer |\n\n#### E. Secondary Workspace (MiniMax)\nLocated at `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/`:\n- `changes/AR-037/` -- proposal.md, delta-spec.md, tasks.md (different content from primary workspace)\n- `example/pcap-analyzer/` (hyphen variant) -- pcap_analyzer.py, requirements.txt, Dockerfile, deployment.yaml, README.md, __init__.py (NO tests subdirectory)\n- `tests/test_pcap_analyzer.py` -- separate test file at project root level\n\n#### F. Session Log Files\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/results/runs/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z_logs/AR-037_ST-{0..6}.log` -- 7 session logs for the primary workspace\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/results/runs/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z_logs/AR-037_ST-{0..7}.log` -- 8 session logs for the MiniMax workspace\n\n---\n\n### 2. What Features Were Implemented\n\nThe implementation is a **hybrid** application that combines two distinct paradigms:\n\n#### A. FastAPI Web Service (Primary implementation in both workspaces)\n- **`POST /analyze` endpoint** -- accepts PCAP file uploads or file paths via form data\n- **LangChain/LangGraph agent orchestration**:\n  - `Planner Agent` -- generates Python analysis scripts using LLM\n  - `Reporter Agent` -- generates human-readable reports from execution results\n  - `ReAct Agent` -- coordinates the planning-execution-reporting flow\n- **`SandboxRunner` class** -- wraps `CodeInterpreterClient` for sandbox operations:\n  - `upload_file()` / `upload_bytes()` -- file staging to sandbox\n  - `run()` -- command execution in sandbox\n  - `stop()` -- cleanup\n- **Automatic script repair** -- `_analyze_with_retries()` retries with repaired scripts on failure (max 2 retries)\n- **Configuration via environment variables**: `OPENAI_API_KEY`, `OPENAI_API_BASE`, `OPENAI_MODEL`, `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME`, `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE`, `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC`\n- **Startup validation** -- requires `OPENAI_API_KEY` or raises `ValueError`\n\n#### B. CLI Script (Spec-compliant portion, also in primary workspace)\n- **`argparse` CLI** with arguments: `--pcap-file`, `--output`, `--top-n`, `--timeline-interval`, `--verbose`\n- **`ANALYSIS_SCRIPT` constant** -- embedded scapy-based Python script for PCAP analysis:\n  - Protocol distribution (TCP/UDP/ICMP/DNS/HTTP)\n  - Top N source/destination IPs\n  - Traffic timeline buckets\n- **`analyze_pcap()` function** -- full orchestration:\n  - Validates PCAP file exists\n  - Uses `CodeInterpreterClient` context manager\n  - Uploads PCAP to sandbox\n  - Installs scapy if needed\n  - Runs analysis script\n  - Checks for tshark and runs optional filters\n  - Writes JSON results\n  - Prints formatted summary\n- **Helper functions**: `validate_pcap_file()`, `check_python_version()`, `check_tshark_available()`, `run_tshark_filter()`, `print_analysis_summary()`\n- **Entry point**: `python pcap_analyzer.py` (CLI mode) or `python pcap_analyzer.py --serve` (FastAPI mode)\n\n#### C. Container & Deployment\n- **Dockerfile** -- uv-based Python 3.12 image, vendors agentcube SDK, exposes port 8000\n- **Kubernetes deployment.yaml** -- Deployment + Secret, resource requests/limits, environment variable wiring\n\n#### D. Test Suite (Primary workspace only)\n- **37 tests total** across 3 test files, all passing\n- Tests cover: agent building, script planning/repair, sandbox runner, configuration, FastAPI endpoints\n\n---\n\n### 3. What Was Deferred or Left Incomplete\n\n#### A. Tasks Not Completed (from `tasks.md`)\nAll 13 tasks (T-1 through T-13) remain **unchecked** in the primary workspace. The implementation was done but task tracking was never updated.\n\n#### B. Missing `sample_traffic.pcap`\n- The spec requires a sample PCAP file (`< 1MB`) at `examples/pcap_analyzer/sample_traffic.pcap`\n- **File does NOT exist** in either workspace\n- Task T-10 (sample PCAP generation script) was never implemented\n\n#### C. Missing `generate_sample.py`\n- Task T-10 calls for a script to generate sample PCAP traffic using scapy\n- **File does NOT exist** in either workspace\n\n#### D. Spec Deviations (from verification report)\n| Requirement | Status | Details |\n|---|---|---|\n| Package structure | FAIL | Spec: `sdk-python/examples/pcap_analyzer/`. Actual: `example/pcap_analyzer/` |\n| `sample_traffic.pcap` | FAIL | File missing |\n| Dependencies | FAIL | Spec: \"only stdlib + agentcube-sdk\". Actual: 15 deps (FastAPI, LangChain, etc.) |\n| CLI script style | PARTIAL | CLI functions exist but secondary to FastAPI+LLM service not in spec |\n| `AUTH_TOKEN` env var | MINOR | Mentioned in spec, not explicitly handled |\n| Test: CLI arg parsing | MISSING | Not in test suite |\n| Test: missing ROUTER_URL | MISSING | Not in test suite |\n| Test: missing PCAP file | MISSING | Not in test suite |\n| Test: empty PCAP | MISSING | Not in test suite |\n\n#### E. Secondary Workspace (MiniMax) Gaps\n- No tests subdirectory in `example/pcap-analyzer/`\n- `requirements.txt` has fewer dependencies (no scapy, no langgraph packages)\n- `SandboxRunner` lacks `__enter__`/`__exit__` context manager support (confirmed via grep)\n- Tasks in `tasks.md` remain unchecked\n\n#### F. Other Deferred Items (from AR-036 archive that also covers PCAP)\n- OAuth integration -- commented out in provider descriptor\n- Icon assets -- `icon.png` and `icon-dark.png` not present\n- Large file handling -- edge cases not explicitly verified\n- Invalid PCAP error handling -- not explicitly verified\n\n---\n\n### 4. Overall State of This Work\n\n**Status: Substantially implemented but with notable gaps.**\n\nThe AR-037 PCAP analyzer example application exists in two variants across two benchmark workspaces:\n\n1. **Primary workspace** (`opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus`): More complete implementation with 37 passing tests, both CLI and FastAPI modes, full LangChain/LangGraph agent orchestration, but deviates from the original spec (which called for a simple CLI script using only stdlib + agentcube-sdk).\n\n2. **Secondary workspace** (`opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5`): Simpler FastAPI-only implementation without the CLI mode, fewer dependencies, no test subdirectory, and missing context manager support on SandboxRunner.\n\n**Key tension**: The original spec (proposal.md) envisioned a simple CLI script demonstrating `CodeInterpreterClient` usage with minimal dependencies. The actual implementation evolved into a much more complex FastAPI + LLM agent orchestration service with 15+ dependencies. The CLI functionality exists in the primary workspace but is secondary to the web service.\n\n**What works**: The core application code is functional, tests pass, container and K8s configs are in place, and the spec verification confirmed that key interfaces (`analyze_pcap()`, `ANALYSIS_SCRIPT`, CLI arguments, tshark helpers, output formatting) match the design spec.\n\n**What is missing**: The sample PCAP file, the sample generation script, task checkbox updates, and several edge-case tests.\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_284f1558affeWjyQABi7XgNSyq","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore AR-037 PCAP analyzer","time":{"start":1775886051955,"end":1775886194341}}}}
